[[File:ConnerNet-FF134.png|thumb|right|250px|A Conner net being deployed]]
A '''Conner net''' was a missile-launched weapon, developed by [[Conner Ship Systems]], that unfurled into a wide swath of highly charged gossamer material. When it hit a ship it discharged, shorting out any operative systems and leaving the ship stranded in space. They could be negated by [[cap drain]]s.

[[File:ConnerNetCanister-FF134.png|thumb|left|A Conner net canister prior to deployment]]
Conner nets were a favorite of ship thieves like [[Niles Ferrier]], as they could disable a ship without causing any physical damage, and could be concealed more easily than an [[Ion cannon/Legends|ion cannon]]. Small Conner nets could be used as traps against intruders. In this application, they could be quite deadly.

The [[Chiss Expansionary Defense Force|CEDF]] employed kilometer-wide '''shock nets''', which operated on similar principles but were larger than any Conner nets available in the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] as of [[27 BBY/Legends|27 BBY]]. Conner nets also existed in [[APNG3|antipersonnel]] versions, fired from guns that were attachable to battle armors.

==Behind the scenes==
The sourcebook [[Galladinium's Fantastic Technology]], and the novel [[Outbound Flight (novel)|''Outbound Flight'']], misspell the device's name "'''Connor net'''."

